Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteIoRowFiller(25.10)                              deleteIoRowFiller(25.10)

Name
       deleteIoRowFiller - Deletes the I/O row filler cells

Syntax
        deleteIoRowFiller

       [-help]

       -cell {<fillerCellNameList> ...}

        [-logic]

       [-prefix <prefix>]

       [-ioRow <name>]

       [-from <coord>] [-to <coord>]

       Deletes the I/O row filler cells. You can use this command at any point
       in the design flow.

Parameters
       -cell {<fillerCellNameList> ...}
              Specifies  the name of the filler cell(s) to delete from the I/O
              row.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -from <coord>
              Specifies the coordinates of a specified  starting  range  where
              I/O  filler  cells are to be deleted. The values are in microme-
              ters.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each deleteNetWeight parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all of its  parameters,  use  the
              man command:

              man deleteNetWeight

       -ioRow <name>
              Specifies the name of the I/O row to delete the filler cell.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -logic Deletes non-physical I/O fillers.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -prefix <prefix>
              Specifies  the  prefix name to be appended to the I/O row filler
              cell to be deleted.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -to <coord>
              Specifies the coordinates of a specified ending range where  I/O
              row filler cells to be deleted. The values are in micrometers.

              Data_type: float, optional

Example
              * The following command deletes the specified I/O instance.

                deleteIoRowFiller -cell PAD8 -prefix PAD8

Related Information
              * createIoRow

              * addIoRowFiller

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

                * Performing I/O Row Based Pad Placement

